comments: I took Fitch many years ago & thought all these comments were hilarious and accurate This man prepped me for medicine..I\'m just finishing my didactic year in the Physician Assistant program & his class was harder than some I am taking now. If you want to KNOW, and I mean REALLY know the stuff, take him. If you\'re trying to get a free ride, don\'t.

stu_tags: BEWARE OF POP QUIZZES  TOUGH GRADER  GET READY TO READ
comments: Fitch tells you 1st thing in semester, "sacrifice work for school, you don\'t want to deliver pizzas the rest of your life". VERBATIM. And he is serious. Treats every student like they are all going into nursing school so tries to make it comparable. If u are nursing, great--but some aren\'t. By far the hardest class I\'ve ever had, learned a lot tho.

comments: Fitch is a very intelligent man, would I take again? No. His lectures are FASCINATING but they rarely pertain to the what we need to know. Lecture tests are VERY hard. Doesn\'t tell you what to know for tests, which is stressful for labs. Gives pop quizzes the day after starting new material. Have perfect attendance if you want a shot at xtra credit
